00:30:47.610 --> 00:30:49.330
I'm going to talk a little
bit about Local Contexts

00:30:49.330 --> 00:30:53.530
which was developed in
2012 as a digital platform

00:30:53.530 --> 00:30:56.430
to create different
kinds of pathways

00:30:56.430 --> 00:30:59.200
for indigenous communities to
deal with intellectual property

00:30:59.200 --> 00:31:01.960
around the collections that they
don't necessarily hold legal

00:31:01.960 --> 00:31:05.190
title over and yet are
the cultural authorities

00:31:05.190 --> 00:31:08.620
and are not recognized as such
in the archives, libraries

00:31:08.620 --> 00:31:10.750
and museums in this country
and around the world.

00:31:10.750 --> 00:31:15.290
This project really
began because we knew

00:31:15.290 --> 00:31:16.590
that there was a
really big problem

00:31:16.590 --> 00:31:18.230
that indigenous communities
were, have been [facing],

00:31:18.230 --> 00:31:20.630
particularly as this
material is being digitized

00:31:20.630 --> 00:31:22.010
and re-circulated ...

00:31:22.010 --> 00:31:26.320
problems in the original records
- that those names of the people

00:31:26.320 --> 00:31:29.310
who were integral
to the production

00:31:29.310 --> 00:31:31.430
of those materials
were not recorded

00:31:31.430 --> 00:31:32.730
at that particular time.

00:31:32.730 --> 00:31:36.280
And so as this material became
digitized, those names continued

00:31:36.280 --> 00:31:38.490
to not circulate
with that material.

00:31:38.490 --> 00:31:42.490
So the Local Contexts platform
has two major components.

00:31:42.490 --> 00:31:44.970
The first part is an
educational component.

00:31:44.970 --> 00:31:48.300
It does a lot of
work educating tribes

00:31:48.300 --> 00:31:49.760
around Intellectual
Property law.

00:31:49.760 --> 00:31:51.410
It provides template documents.

00:31:51.410 --> 00:31:53.820
It provides a whole
range of training modules

00:31:53.820 --> 00:31:55.650
around intellectual property.

00:31:55.650 --> 00:31:56.950
And the other part

00:31:56.950 --> 00:32:00.710
of the platform are these
Traditional Knowledge labels.

00:32:00.710 --> 00:32:05.670
These really might be understood
as digital tags or protocols,

00:32:05.670 --> 00:32:07.080
community protocols
that have been,

00:32:07.080 --> 00:32:10.720
that have taken a digital form
which allow for a protocol

00:32:10.720 --> 00:32:14.310
to travel with material, to
travel with a digital item.

00:32:14.310 --> 00:32:18.670
We have seventeen labels that
we've developed in collaboration

00:32:18.670 --> 00:32:19.970
with about the twenty
communities

00:32:19.970 --> 00:32:22.660
that we have been working
with over the last four years.

00:32:22.660 --> 00:32:24.520
And they range on a
spectrum, I'm not really going

00:32:24.520 --> 00:32:26.630
to show them to you, but
they range on a spectrum

00:32:26.630 --> 00:32:30.150
from multiple communities
or a label that indicates

00:32:30.150 --> 00:32:31.450
that there are multiple
communities

00:32:31.450 --> 00:32:34.490
that have responsibility
over certain kind of piece

00:32:34.490 --> 00:32:36.400
of heritage to secret,

00:32:36.400 --> 00:32:41.490
sacred material to...culturally
sensitive material

00:32:41.490 --> 00:32:45.290
to attribution to outreach.

00:32:45.290 --> 00:32:46.670
There's seventeen there

00:32:46.670 --> 00:32:50.680
and they're all...what they
do is they provide nuance

00:32:50.680 --> 00:32:53.120
in how indigenous communities
would like that material

00:32:53.120 --> 00:32:54.690
to be circulated
into the future.

