00:43:29.840 --> 00:43:33.600
So Mukurtu CMS, like
I said, it's a free

00:43:33.600 --> 00:43:35.300
and open source content
management system,

00:43:35.300 --> 00:43:37.960
but there's four things
that set Mukurtu apart.

00:43:37.960 --> 00:43:41.420
And like I said, it grew out of
my work in central Australia.

00:43:41.420 --> 00:43:43.430
Mukurtu literally
means "dilly bag"

00:43:43.430 --> 00:43:46.080
and a dilly bag is a
safe keeping place.

00:43:46.080 --> 00:43:50.350
So for the Warumungu people who
I started working with in 1995

00:43:50.350 --> 00:43:52.320
to build this, this
was the idea:

00:43:52.320 --> 00:43:55.280
to create a digital safe
keeping place - that same sort

00:43:55.280 --> 00:43:57.330
of keeping place
that that dilly bag

00:43:57.330 --> 00:43:59.100
that held those sacred items.

00:43:59.100 --> 00:44:02.500
So what Mukurtu, the
content management system -

00:44:02.500 --> 00:44:04.250
there are four things that
sort of set it apart -

00:44:04.250 --> 00:44:06.980
we have this cultural
protocol based access.

00:44:06.980 --> 00:44:09.940
So what Donald was
saying, how do we ensure

00:44:09.940 --> 00:44:12.960
that the protocols we
already have offline are

00:44:12.960 --> 00:44:14.300
respected online.

00:44:14.300 --> 00:44:16.950
So Mukurtu allows that
for any community.

00:44:16.950 --> 00:44:19.800
We also have multiple
records and extended metadata.

00:44:19.800 --> 00:44:21.100
So you'll see in a minute

00:44:21.100 --> 00:44:24.370
that any one item can
have multiple records

00:44:24.370 --> 00:44:27.330
because as we've seen, this
trading song isn't just

00:44:27.330 --> 00:44:31.410
that one record with one
authoritative voice telling us

00:44:31.410 --> 00:44:32.710
about that.

00:44:32.710 --> 00:44:34.720
. And we have a suite
of functions,

00:44:34.720 --> 00:44:37.590
that we call round trip, that
allows you to get things easily

00:44:37.590 --> 00:44:40.770
in and out and share them
with other institutions -

00:44:40.770 --> 00:44:43.410
specifically though,
using selective sync.

00:44:43.410 --> 00:44:45.890
So if the Passamaquoddy don't
want to share everything,

00:44:45.890 --> 00:44:47.240
then they don't have to.

00:44:47.240 --> 00:44:48.540
So that's built in.

00:44:48.540 --> 00:44:50.430
And then, of course,
finally, the TK labels.

00:44:50.430 --> 00:44:53.680
So all of these come around
in the Passamaquoddy site,

00:44:53.680 --> 00:44:56.070
which you can see here,
"Passamaquoddy people:

00:44:56.070 --> 00:44:57.720
At home on the Ocean and Lakes",

