Passamaquoddy made to...really

00:47:36.120 --> 00:47:39.400
let people know why are there
these labels, when you get

00:47:39.400 --> 00:47:43.160
to a record, what -why are there
these labels and what are they?

00:47:43.160 --> 00:47:46.120
So you can see on this page,
there's an explanation,

00:47:46.120 --> 00:47:49.200
not only the translation
into Passamaquoddy and then

00:47:49.200 --> 00:47:52.820
into English of what that means,
but also a section on, well,

00:47:52.820 --> 00:47:54.190
why did we want to use these?

00:47:54.190 --> 00:47:58.250
And as Donald said at the
beginning, the contextualization

00:47:58.250 --> 00:48:01.370
at the top is that we're
the rightful owners

00:48:01.370 --> 00:48:04.150
of these materials, we're
the cultural authorities,

00:48:04.150 --> 00:48:05.450
no matter who the sort

00:48:05.450 --> 00:48:07.860
of western legal
copyright holder is.

00:48:07.860 --> 00:48:09.690
So it's really bringing
us back to that

00:48:09.690 --> 00:48:12.770
and that was very purposeful
and I'm sure if I'm Donald wants

00:48:12.770 --> 00:48:14.630
to talk about that
later, he can.

00:48:14.630 --> 00:48:18.090
[With] each of the labels
