01:09:02.680 --> 01:09:05.260
because nothing ever
circulates, right?

01:09:05.260 --> 01:09:08.040
I mean in a Western
sense, we think of objects

01:09:08.040 --> 01:09:09.510
that circulate out of that.

01:09:09.510 --> 01:09:12.960
So Mukurtu puts that into a
context, so every single item

01:09:12.960 --> 01:09:16.720
in any Mukurtu system has
to be enabled to actually

01:09:16.720 --> 01:09:20.180
to upload it, you have to have
a who and a how - a community

01:09:20.180 --> 01:09:22.810
and how do you want it
accessed - and so the who

01:09:22.810 --> 01:09:25.100
and the how is decided
by the Passmaquoddy.

01:09:25.100 --> 01:09:27.750
So you were seeing the
public site without a log in,

01:09:27.750 --> 01:09:30.250
so that's already
been vetted and,

01:09:30.250 --> 01:09:33.240
enabled to see- the login
will be the community members

01:09:33.240 --> 01:09:36.990
and that's determined
by the community.

