01:15:57.870 --> 01:16:00.170
&gt;&gt; Donald Soctomah: Well,

01:16:02.970 --> 01:16:06.490
I think this material
was developed

01:16:06.490 --> 01:16:11.370
because our tribe is a
sharing type of tribe.

01:16:11.370 --> 01:16:15.780
Members of our tribe would
give the shirt off their back

01:16:15.780 --> 01:16:18.180
for anybody, and I think

01:16:18.180 --> 01:16:22.680
when the ancestors were sharing
the song, sharing the stories,

01:16:22.680 --> 01:16:23.980
that's what they
were doing was...

01:16:23.980 --> 01:16:30.290
sharing. When Fewkes came back
a couple months later [in 1890]

01:16:30.290 --> 01:16:34.870
to play the wax cylinders
back to the tribe, you know,

01:16:34.870 --> 01:16:37.970
nobody's ever heard this before.

01:16:37.970 --> 01:16:41.510
I just can imagine what
they were thinking -

01:16:41.510 --> 01:16:44.660
hearing their own
voices, you know,

01:16:44.660 --> 01:16:47.460
nobody's ever heard
their voices before!

01:16:47.460 --> 01:16:49.010
And then they were
the first ones

01:16:49.010 --> 01:16:53.910
to hear their voices playing
back, singing back, you know,

01:16:53.910 --> 01:16:55.220
what were they thinking?

01:16:55.220 --> 01:16:57.570
what was going through
their mind...

01:16:57.570 --> 01:17:00.610
this, the world changing.

01:17:00.610 --> 01:17:04.100
You know, it was right at that
moment the world was changing

01:17:04.100 --> 01:17:08.540
for them and I think
they realized we have

01:17:08.540 --> 01:17:11.010
to continue to share.

01:17:11.010 --> 01:17:13.890
Because if you look at the
timeline for the tribe right

01:17:13.890 --> 01:17:18.460
after that, Charles Leland
wrote the Algonquian legends

01:17:18.460 --> 01:17:20.910
and the tribe shared
most of those stories

01:17:20.910 --> 01:17:24.990
on the Algonquian legends,
they're the stories of the,

01:17:24.990 --> 01:17:28.920
mainly the Passamaquoddy,
and a few other tribes.

01:17:28.920 --> 01:17:31.950
The tribe started
sharing, sharing stories -

01:17:31.950 --> 01:17:36.540
continued on some of the older
..well, younger recordings

01:17:36.540 --> 01:17:41.210
from 1947 ended up at
the Library of Congress

01:17:41.210 --> 01:17:43.410
and the tribe kept sharing.

01:17:43.410 --> 01:17:47.930
So that good will
of our tribe is sort

01:17:47.930 --> 01:17:52.140
of saving the songs
for the future.

01:17:52.140 --> 01:17:55.730
And just that good will..

